Pyrrhus: the Greek word from which the name Pyrrhus is derived means ‘red' ‘dame-colored‚’ hence Macaulay calls him ‘the red king) With the story of Pyrrhus we reach the domain of historical truth. He was one of the greatest generals of an- tiquity, and one of the best kings. He was regarded by the Romans of later times with kindly feelings. Cicero refers t0 the war with Pyrrhus as ‘a struggle fordominion with a noble and powerful king,' and relates many anecdotes of his chivalrous conduct.
